1
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,000
Are you

2
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:11,960
going home?

3
00:01:13,039 --> 00:01:13,920
No.

4
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:16,880
This was donated to me by someone else.

5
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:17,680
Just take it.

6
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:19,320
Okay.

7
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,370
That is very thoughtful of you.

8
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,400
The documents are ready for you, Sanxi.

9
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:29,840
Only 16 years old.

10
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,850
It builds virtue for our descendants.

11
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:34,759
We can't just leave her to die.

12
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:38,080
But buying her freedom costs at least

13
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,210
500 silver dollars.

14
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,320
We poor patrolmen

15
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,360
only make 14 dollars a month.

16
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,600
One dollar

17
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:46,960
isn't too little.

18
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,360
Ten dollars

19
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:49,580
isn't too much.

20
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,120
Every little bit counts.

21
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,850
We'll eventually have enough.

22
00:01:55,039 --> 00:01:56,039
Hurry.

23
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:09,000
I saw it.

24
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:11,720
What do you mean?

25
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:15,330
Is the Police Station meddling in brothel business?

26
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,720
Don't forget,

27
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,000
the prostitution licenses

28
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,520
were issued by us.

29
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:28,520
She's only sixteen.

30
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,620
It's good karma for our descendants.

31
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,880
We can't just leave her to die.

32
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,640
I'm off duty now.

33
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:54,360
I represent only myself.

34
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,820
It has nothing to do with the Police Station.

35
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:57,600
Thank you.

36
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,090
It's too old.

37
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,040
Pawn it for me.

38
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,480
Just in time.

39
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,320
You really wrecked my show.

40
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,640
You owe me an explanation.

41
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,280
Fine.

42
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,560
We'll give you an explanation right now.

43
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:42,280
We suspect you of illegally abducting women.

44
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:43,120
We also found out...

45
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,840
...that five years ago, you and Yan Wenjun...

46
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,720
...sexually assaulted Guan Sinian.

47
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:48,360
You are now under arrest.

48
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,880
How can the police frame an innocent man like this?

49
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:55,210
Resisting arrest, huh?

50
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,320
Open the door.

51
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:00,600
Her...

52
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,960
You're not taking her.

53
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,280
The debt she owes

54
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,010
is enough to feed you for years.

55
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,280
It's just money, isn't it?

56
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:07,880
We have it.

57
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,240
Bring out her indenture and the debt records.

58
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,120
Let's settle this now.

59
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,980
Don't come asking for more later.

60
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,400
What are you waiting for?

61
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,120
Go.

62
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:05,400
Come.

63
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:08,120
I'll take you away from here.

64
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:35,440
Grandpa.

65
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,200
What is it?

66
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:56,320
What's wrong?

67
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,740
Where are my slippers?

68
00:05:59,360 --> 00:05:59,960
Slippers.

69
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,320
For today,

70
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:30,840
tomato ribs.

71
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,200
How does that sound?

72
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,080
Splendid.

73
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,400
You got it.

74
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,440
I'm sorry.

75
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,980
I really didn't mean to steal your child.

76
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:08,240
Alright.

77
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,000
Just three.

78
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,080
Let's go.

79
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:12,280
Sorry about that.

80
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,000
Grandpa,

81
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,000
what is it now?

82
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,480
What is it now?

83
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,280
My hair tie is gone.

84
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,140
I can't find it.

85
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,440
Hair tie.

86
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,159
Here.

87
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:58,920
Without me,

88
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,760
can you not even leave the house?

89
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,400
Grandpa, look what a good deal this is.

90
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,160
She pays rent and cooks.

91
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,040
Leave it there, kid.

92
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,210
I'll do it later.

93
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,280
No need, Grandpa. I can do it.

94
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,320
Don't they teach physics in France?

95
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:52,960
Rain.

96
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:40,360
Go home.

97
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,000
Don't be afraid.

98
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:45,200
Go home.

99
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,240
Don't be afraid.

100
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,970
The newspaper didn't say it would rain today.

101
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:00,640
Don't trust the newspapers.

102
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,160
It's going to rain heavily soon.

103
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:03,890
Hurry and bring in the laundry.

104
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:07,880
Do you know some kind of sorcery?

105
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:11,680
Swallows fly low, snakes cross the path.

106
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,680
Ants move house, moss grows damp.

107
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:16,840
Ancestral wisdom works better than foreign gadgets.

108
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:00,760
Grandpa, stop hiding it.

109
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:01,800
That's mine.

110
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,480
Whose side are you on?

111
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,720
I'm definitely on your side.

112
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:20,000
Your ribs are delicious.

113
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,240
Deal.

114
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,740
I'll make them for you once a week.

115
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:24,240
Okay.

116
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,520
She's all grown up.

117
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:36,440
I'm afraid she won't need me someday.

118
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,370
Grandpa.

119
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,760
No matter who Qin Xin meets

120
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,200
or where she goes,

121
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:51,360
you'll always be the most important person to her.

122
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,890
She won't stop needing you.

123
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,000
She'll meet more people.

124
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:02,760
But the people I know are all gone.

125
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:07,000
I only have her left.

126
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:13,920
Life...

127
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,200
a lifetime...

128
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,000
passes in the blink of an eye.

129
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:56,240
Xiaoyu, you can take a bath today.

130
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,600
Why don't you fix that window...

131
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,600
I'm not fixing it.

132
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:06,210
Don't try to talk me into it.

133
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:17,810
Why is someone coming here in the middle of the night?

134
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:20,480
Corpse stitchers only work at night.

135
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,860
Can't you install another light?

136
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,760
It's convenient and free.

137
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:32,280
Only you rich people

138
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:33,440
would think that

139
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:35,840
electricity in the Concession is free.

140
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,880
They charge by the number.

141
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,800
One light per household

142
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,840
is five yuan a month.

143
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,760
If this place were brightly lit,

144
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,760
wouldn't that cost several months' wages?

